  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 662de8a6992c486fa87e377ee9253765, type: 3}
  m_Name: UI Framework Agnostic
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::Trailback.Demo.Features.Data.FeatureDemoData
  featureName: UI Framework Agnostic
  shortDescription: Designed to work with a wide range of Unity UI architectures
    and workflows.
  fullDescription: "Trailback is designed to manage navigation without being tied
    to a specific UI implementation.\n\nIt doesn't require your UI to inherit from
    a particular base class, follow a predefined screen architecture, or use a specific
    presentation framework. Instead, Trailback focuses on navigation behavior, making
    it easier to integrate into existing projects without restructuring your UI systems.\n\nTrailback
    has been developed and tested primarily with Unity UGUI and Canvas-based workflows,
    but it can be used with many UI architectures that require:\n\n\u2022 Back Navigation\n\u2022
    Navigation History\n\u2022 Category-Based Resolution\n\u2022 Navigation Blockers\n\nTrailback
    is not a state machine, command system, or undo/redo framework. Its responsibility
    is intentionally focused on navigation management, allowing it to work alongside
    other systems that handle application state, game flow, or business logic.\n\nProjects
    with highly customized UI pipelines or specialized workflow requirements may
    require additional integration, but Trailback is designed to remain flexible
    and adapt to a variety of project structures."
  screenshots: []
  videoUrl: 
  documentationUrl: https://github.com/akpardeshi/Trailback/#what-is-trailback
